<div itemprop="name" class="ERSName">Corn Soup</div> <div class="ERSClear"></div> <div class="ERSDetails"> <div class="ERSClear"></div> <div class="ERSTimes"> <div class="ERSHead"> Prep time:&nbsp; <time itemprop="prepTime" datetime="PT30M">30 mins</time> </div> <div class="ERSHead"> Cook time:&nbsp; <time itemprop="cookTime" datetime="PT30M">30 mins</time> </div> <div class="ERSHead"> Total time:&nbsp; <time itemprop="totalTime" datetime="PT1H">1 hour</time> </div> </div> <div class="ERSClear"></div> <div class="ERSHead"> Serves:&nbsp;<span itemprop="recipeYield">4</span></div> <div class="ERSClear">&nbsp;</div> </div> <div class="ERSIngredients"> <div class="ERSIngredientsHeader ERSHeading">Ingredients</div> <ul> <li class="ingredient" itemprop="ingredients">2 tbs butter</li> <li class="ingredient" itemprop="ingredients">4 corn</li> <li class="ingredient" itemprop="ingredients">2 cup water</li> <li class="ingredient" itemprop="ingredients">2 cup milk (or cream)</li> <li class="ingredient" itemprop="ingredients">1 sp cornstarch + 1 sp water</li> <li class="ingredient" itemprop="ingredients">2-3 cloves garlic</li> <li class="ingredient" itemprop="ingredients">Â½ onion or 1 leek</li> <li class="ingredient" itemprop="ingredients">Salt and pepper</li> <li class="ingredient" itemprop="ingredients">Chives/scallions for garnish</li> <li class="ingredient" itemprop="ingredients">For corn pancakes with leftover: 3 sp flour and 1 egg</li> </ul> <div class="ERSClear"></div> </div> <div class="ERSInstructions"> <div class="ERSInstructionsHeader ERSHeading">Instructions</div> <ol> <li class="instruction" itemprop="recipeInstructions">Using saute mode in Instant Pot, saute chopped onions (or leek) and minced garlic in the butter for 2-3 minutes.</li> <li class="instruction" itemprop="recipeInstructions">Pour in milk and water (you can use cream for a thicker texture). Place corn in the Instant Pot and set to manual mode 10 minutes, then use quick release. This will produce a corn broth.</li> <li class="instruction" itemprop="recipeInstructions">Remove corn cobs from Instant Pot and cut off the kernels. Add kernels back into the Pot, reserving some whole kernels to add into the soup later, and using an immersion blender, blend the soup until a relatively smooth texture is achieved.</li> <li class="instruction" itemprop="recipeInstructions">Strain to remove the corn bits and pieces from the soup.</li> <li class="instruction" itemprop="recipeInstructions">Season soup with salt and pepper. Serve with chopped scallions/chives and some whole kernels.</li> <li class="instruction" itemprop="recipeInstructions">With leftover corn mixture, add 3 sp flour and 1 egg and mix well. Heat 2 sp of oil and fry ~2-inch wide size corn pancakes.</li> </ol> <div class="ERSClear"></div> </div> <div class="ERSNotesDiv"> <div class="ERSNotesHeader">Notes</div> <div class="ERSNotes">sp = 1 dinner spoon</div> <div class="ERSClear"></div> </div> <div class="endeasyrecipe" title="style001" style="display: none">3.5.3239</div> </div>